Overview

So the idea here is that we are going group NBA players into like group using a clustering algorithm The data is scraped from Basketball Reference

Lets take a look at our data.

So it looks like our model has separated the players on skill. Well notice that the

  • Red group (1) are the top players.
  • Blue group (4) are the next best players
  • Green group (3) are likely role players
  • Yellow group (2) are the lower tier players
  • Pink group (5) are likely young players and lower tier palyers.

Now that Ive made the claim let me try and back it up.

Pink Group - 5

df |> 
  filter(clus_5 == "5") |> 
  summarise(
    centers = sum(pos_C),
    power_forwards = sum(pos_PF),
    small_forwards = sum(pos_SF),
    shooting_guards = sum(pos_SG),
    point_guards = sum(pos_PG)
  )
## # A tibble: 1  5
##   centers power_forwards small_forwards shooting_guards point_guards
##     <int>          <int>          <int>           <int>        <int>
## 1      22             24             26              38           24

A lot of shooting guards in this group but then again there are more shooting guards in the league than anything else as we saw above.

I called this group either 1 of 2 things. Lower Tier players or younger players. So lets take a look at the general ages of the players.
